DataElementConcept.preferredName: Protocol Disposition Event Or Protocol Milestone Begin
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: The group of incidents that occur during a clinical trial and describe whether a subject completed the study epoch or the reason this event did not occur. The subject's disposition is often described for each phase of the study._An article used to connect words, phrases, or clauses representing alternatives; used to connect alternative terms for the same thing; used in correlation; used to correct or rephrase what was previously said; otherwise._Occurrences within some epochs that are initiated by a protocol-specified event. The most common protocol milestone is "Informed Consent Obtained" which usually documents the start of the study._Have a beginning, in a temporal, spatial, or evaluative sense; the point in space or time where something begins.
